\begin{align*}
6x\amp=-46\\
x\amp=-\frac{23}{3}
\end{align*}
Since $P=(a,b)$ and $a=x$, we have $a=-\frac{23}{3}$. Substituting into either equation to solve for $b$ produces:
\begin{align*}
b\amp=2\left(-\frac{23}{3}\right)-10\\
\amp=-\frac{46}{3}-\frac{30}{3}\\
\amp=-\frac{76}{3}
\end{align*}
